Overnight, the verdant wetland in Saihanba National Forest Park in China's Hebei Province turned into a world of ice and snow. Everywhere you look, it's white. The vast grassland is covered thickly with snow. Herbivores struggle to find plants to eat. Check the video to see more. About 'Journeys in Nature': Hebei series Hebei Province in north China hosts the largest forest park in northern China, Saihanba National Forest Park, and the country's largest expanse of coastal sand dunes, the Golden Coast National Nature Reserve. Here, you will find unique landforms and a rich variety of plants and animals. For more: Hebei series | Episode 1: Beautiful Highland Hebei series | Episode 2: Boundary River (Cover image via a screenshot) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)